RDNA4 (gfx1201) fix: Mamba2/SSD chunk-scan + chunk-state divergent fat-pointer
crashes the AMD buffer-ops pass, capping hybrid SSM models at ~8K context.

Two SSD Triton kernels reassign a state pointer to a DIFFERENT base tensor inside
an `if` branch and use it after the merge:
  - ssd_chunk_scan.py  _chunk_scan_fwd_kernel : prev_states_ptr  (states vs initstates)
  - ssd_chunk_state.py _chunk_state_varlen_kernel : past_states_ptrs (chunk_states vs initstates)
Both only take that branch when initial_states != None, i.e. exactly the chunked-
prefill / continuous-batching path a long sequence hits. With AMD buffer ops on
(the default, AMDGCN_USE_BUFFER_OPS=1), TritonAMDGPUCanonicalizePointers must
decompose the post-merge pointer into a (base, 32-bit offset) "fat pointer", but
the two branches have different bases -> assertion
  `fatPtrs.at(then)==fatPtrs.at(else)` (canNarrow) -> PassManager::run failed -> abort.
This capped Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni-30B (first Mamba2 hybrid on the box) at ~8K.

Fix: keep every pointer SINGLE-BASED. Record the branch decision in a runtime flag
+ index, build both candidate tile pointers independently, load both (masked), and
select the VALUE with tl.where at the matmul site. Numerically identical to upstream
(validated BIT-EXACT with buffer ops off; buffer-ops-on differs only by the buffer
codegen's own rounding, rel<=2.2e-4 << bf16 eps). Buffer ops stay ENABLED everywhere
(full perf) -- this is a kernel fix, not a buffer-ops disable. Pure RDNA4 codegen
workaround; semantics unchanged on CUDA. Applies to ANY Mamba2/SSD hybrid using
initial_states (chunked prefill / cont-batch), not just Nemotron-Omni.

